223
00:51:43,964 --> 00:51:50,329
based on the terseness of the passage and what we know about them, I think not.

224
00:51:50,379 --> 00:51:56,743
What do we know about these two and what led them to respond the way they did?

225
00:51:56,793 --> 00:52:03,157
I want to spend just a couple minutes going over their attributes and their attitude.

226
00:52:03,207 --> 00:52:09,571
It's a model for how we can respond when God is calling us.

227
00:52:09,621 --> 00:52:15,986
(Missional.

228
00:52:16,036 --> 00:52:22,400
Available.

229
00:52:22,450 --> 00:52:28,814
Compassionate.

230
00:52:28,864 --> 00:52:35,228
Flexible.

231
00:52:35,278 --> 00:52:41,643
Heart of servant.

232
00:52:41,693 --> 00:52:48,057
Willing.

233
00:52:48,107 --> 00:52:54,471
Adaptable.

234
00:52:54,521 --> 00:53:00,885
Selfless.) Barnabas - name meant -"Son of Encouragement" - And he certainly lived up to

235
00:53:00,935 --> 00:53:07,300
his name.

236
00:53:07,350 --> 00:53:13,714
He was the one who was sent from the Jerusalem church to check out the Antioch Church,

237
00:53:13,764 --> 00:53:20,128
but they did not send him only to examine them but to encourage and support them.

238
00:53:20,178 --> 00:53:26,542
We see in him a willing to serve others.

239
00:53:26,592 --> 00:53:32,957
And Barnabas was the one who recruited and sought out Saul/Paul for additional help.

240
00:53:33,007 --> 00:53:39,371
Paul - had an infamous past as a persecutor to the church.

241
00:53:39,421 --> 00:53:45,785
In fact, it is ironic that he was part of the persecution of Stephen that drove the

242
00:53:45,835 --> 00:53:52,199
Jewish believers to Antioch to found this very church that he is serving in.

243
00:53:52,249 --> 00:53:58,614
Paul's persecution of the early church was so intense that after his conversion that his

244
00:53:58,664 --> 00:54:05,028
persecution stopped that there was some semblance of peace in the churches throughout

245
00:54:05,078 --> 00:54:11,442
Galilee and Samaria!!!

246
00:54:11,492 --> 00:54:17,856
(and it said in Acts 9:31 ESV "So the church throughout all Judea and Galilee and Samaria

247
00:54:17,906 --> 00:54:24,271
had peace and was being built up.

248
00:54:24,321 --> 00:54:30,685
And walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit, it

249
00:54:30,735 --> 00:54:37,099
multiplied.").

250
00:54:37,149 --> 00:54:43,513
Also, when Paul was zapped and blinded by Jesus and sent to Ananias to be healed, Ananias

251
00:54:43,563 --> 00:54:49,928
was afraid of him.

252
00:54:49,978 --> 00:54:56,342
But Jesus said to Ananias: Acts 9:15 ESV But the Lord said to him, "Go, for he is a

253
00:54:56,392 --> 00:55:02,756
chosen instrument of mine to carry my name before the Gentiles and kings and the children

254
00:55:02,806 --> 00:55:09,170
of Israel.

255
00:55:09,220 --> 00:55:15,585
Paul was an instrument of Jesus to proclaim His name In Ch 11, Paul, for his part, was

256
00:55:15,635 --> 00:55:21,999
willing to drop whatever he was doing in Tarsus and go with Barnabas to assist the Antioch

257
00:55:22,049 --> 00:55:28,413
church.

258
00:55:28,463 --> 00:55:34,828
Paul was a consummate teacher and spent his energy preaching and teaching about Jesus.

259
00:55:34,878 --> 00:55:41,242
And the both of them threw themselves into the ministry alongside the Antioch church.

260
00:55:41,292 --> 00:55:47,656
And now in ch 13, we see them submitting to the calling of the Holy Spirit to be 'sent" I

261
00:55:47,706 --> 00:55:54,070
just want to highlight some of their attributes: They were clearly missional minded -

262
00:55:54,120 --> 00:56:00,485
willing to share the Gospel to everyone and anyone.

263
00:56:00,535 --> 00:56:06,899
They made themselves available.

264
00:56:06,949 --> 00:56:13,313
Their agenda was God's agenda.

265
00:56:13,363 --> 00:56:19,727
And they showed a willingness to serve wherever God sent them.

266
00:56:19,777 --> 00:56:26,142
They were flexible.

267
00:56:26,192 --> 00:56:32,556
They were adaptable.

268
00:56:32,606 --> 00:56:38,970
They were willing to drop their agenda, their schedules, whatever they were doing to

269
00:56:39,020 --> 00:56:45,384
serve the Lord.

270
00:56:45,434 --> 00:56:51,799
This is a key trait for missionaries.

271
00:56:51,849 --> 00:56:58,213
Something I've heard and learned over and over again in the field.

272
00:56:58,263 --> 00:57:04,627
Because you can make all the plans you want, but you don't know how God will use you once

273
00:57:04,677 --> 00:57:11,041
you get out there.

274
00:57:11,091 --> 00:57:17,456
They were willing to be sent.

275
00:57:17,506 --> 00:57:23,870
Barnabas from the Jerusalem Church.

276
00:57:23,920 --> 00:57:30,284
And here, he was again sent from the Antioch Church.

277
00:57:30,334 --> 00:57:36,698
Paul, followed after the way of Jesus - I don't think he had his own home.

278
00:57:36,748 --> 00:57:43,113
From the moment of his conversion on the road to Damascus, Paul was always on the move to

279
00:57:43,163 --> 00:57:49,527
share the Gospel message, proclaiming the risen Christ throughout the Roman world, up

280
00:57:49,577 --> 00:57:55,941
until he was martyred in Rome.

281
00:57:55,991 --> 00:58:02,355
They both were selfless and had the heart of a servant.

282
00:58:02,405 --> 00:58:08,770
Paul embodied the term, "A living sacrifice" - he fully lived the "surrendered life." We

283
00:58:08,820 --> 00:58:15,184
know that multiple times, Paul suffered for the Gospel.

284
00:58:15,234 --> 00:58:21,598
In 1 Corinthians 11, Paul recounts that he was flogged multiple times, beaten with rods,

285
00:58:21,648 --> 00:58:28,012
pelted with stones, shipwrecked, imprisoned multiple times, and left for dead.

286
00:58:28,062 --> 00:58:34,427
Yet amazingly, he remained faithful to Jesus and to his calling to minister to the

287
00:58:34,477 --> 00:58:40,841
Gentiles.

288
00:58:40,891 --> 00:58:47,255
In his letter to the Philippians he wrote "For to me to live is Christ, and to die is

289
00:58:47,305 --> 00:58:53,669
gain." These are all attributes and attitudes that we should have in common when

290
00:58:53,719 --> 00:59:00,084
responding to God's call for us.

291
00:59:00,134 --> 00:59:06,498
But are we all called to go?

292
00:59:06,548 --> 00:59:12,912
Are we all "called to Missions, specifically cross-cultural missions" - Here's our last

293
00:59:12,962 --> 00:59:19,326
topic - What's my Mission in the Great Commission?

294
00:59:19,376 --> 00:59:25,741
The Great Commission one more time - (show it) Your Mission in the Great Commission All

295
00:59:25,791 --> 00:59:32,155
are called to fulfill the Great Commission some people teach and guilt trip people that

296
00:59:32,205 --> 00:59:38,569
all are called to go on cross-cultural missions - I don't think that's actually right

297
00:59:38,619 --> 00:59:44,983
(phew).

298
00:59:45,033 --> 00:59:51,398
I do believe that all are called to fulfill the Great Commission.

299
00:59:51,448 --> 00:59:57,812
As Rick Warren said, "The Great Commission is not the Great Suggestion." Part of the

300
00:59:57,862 --> 01:00:04,226
Great Commission is of course, sharing the Good News of Jesus locally.

301
01:00:04,276 --> 01:00:10,640
In our community, in our schools, in our work, to our friends, to our families.

302
01:00:10,690 --> 01:00:17,055
Really, the missions field is right at our door and sometimes coming into our doors.

303
01:00:17,105 --> 01:00:23,469
It's our sphere of influence.

304
01:00:23,519 --> 01:00:29,883
The Great Commandment and the Great Commission answers all of life's tough questions.

305
01:00:29,933 --> 01:00:36,297
Why am I here?

306
01:00:36,347 --> 01:00:42,712
What's my purpose in life?

307
01:00:42,762 --> 01:00:49,126
How should I live my life?

308
01:00:49,176 --> 01:00:55,540
The Good News is the Good News for everyone, everywhere, including here.

309
01:00:55,590 --> 01:01:01,954
But we shouldn't stop locally - we do need to participate in God's Global missions.

310
01:01:02,004 --> 01:01:08,369
The Great Commission is active today and continues "to the ends of the earth" But the

311
01:01:08,419 --> 01:01:14,783
Gospel message and God's plan in the Great Commission did not stop at the end of Acts.

312
01:01:14,833 --> 01:01:21,197
God is still at work in the world today!

313
01:01:21,247 --> 01:01:27,611
While some areas are well trodden and the Gospel message is widely available, there are

314
01:01:27,661 --> 01:01:34,026
still many areas of the world that are still unreached.

315
01:01:34,076 --> 01:01:40,440
Many of you are familiar with the 10/40 Window - there is still much of the world that

316
01:01:40,490 --> 01:01:46,854
has not heard.

317
01:01:46,904 --> 01:01:53,268
The green areas are areas which are considered "no longer unreached" where there is a

318
01:01:53,318 --> 01:01:59,683
strong Christian presence.

319
01:01:59,733 --> 01:02:06,097
The Red areas are Unreached People Groups defined as people groups with less than 2%

320
01:02:06,147 --> 01:02:12,511
evangelical Christian populations.

321
01:02:12,561 --> 01:02:18,926
In some of the red areas, there are no known efforts focused on establishing

322
01:02:18,976 --> 01:02:25,340
self-sustaining churches with evangelical faith and practice.

323
01:02:25,390 --> 01:02:31,754
For more details, there's a cool interactive map if you go to peoplegroups.org.

324
01:02:31,804 --> 01:02:38,168
How do I know what my "calling" is?

325
01:02:38,218 --> 01:02:44,583
How do I know if I'm being called to go?

326
01:02:44,633 --> 01:02:50,997
How do I know if and how I'm being called to send?

327
01:02:51,047 --> 01:02:57,411
I want to really take the mystery out of the word "calling." It's a really confusing term

328
01:02:57,461 --> 01:03:03,825
and sometimes, it's frankly misused.

329
01:03:03,875 --> 01:03:10,240
"Calling" or "invitation" in the NT almost always refers to our calling as believers, not

330
01:03:10,290 --> 01:03:16,654
our calling to a specific ministry.

331
01:03:16,704 --> 01:03:23,068
1 Cor 1:2, Ephesians 1:18, Hebrews 3:1 1 Corinthians 1:2 ESV To the church of God that is

332
01:03:23,118 --> 01:03:29,482
in Corinth, to those sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints together with all

333
01:03:29,532 --> 01:03:35,897
those who in every place call upon the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, both their Lord and

334
01:03:35,947 --> 01:03:42,311
ours: Ephesians 1:18 ESV having the eyes of your hearts enlightened, that you may know

335
01:03:42,361 --> 01:03:48,725
what is the hope to which he has called you, what are the riches of his glorious

336
01:03:48,775 --> 01:03:55,139
inheritance in the saints, Hebrews 3:1 ESV Therefore, holy brothers, you who share in a

337
01:03:55,189 --> 01:04:01,554
heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession, So most

338
01:04:01,604 --> 01:04:07,968
of the time - calling refers to a calling of faith, essentially a call to become a

339
01:04:08,018 --> 01:04:14,382
follower of Christ.

340
01:04:14,432 --> 01:04:20,796
Calling is sometimes used improperly to elevate one's spiritual status.

341
01:04:20,846 --> 01:04:27,211
It's as if my "sense" of divine calling to my particular profession obligates others to

342
01:04:27,261 --> 01:04:33,625
treat me in a special way.

343
01:04:33,675 --> 01:04:40,039
OK, so what's the right way to look at what being "called to a particular ministry" means

344
01:04:40,089 --> 01:04:46,453
- How do I know what my "calling" is?

345
01:04:46,503 --> 01:04:52,868
(Being "called to a particular ministry") - In our passage, the Holy Spirit directly

346
01:04:52,918 --> 01:04:59,282
called out Paul and Barnabas for this missions trip.

347
01:04:59,332 --> 01:05:05,696
For almost all of us, our names will not be called out by the Holy Spirit in a prayer

348
01:05:05,746 --> 01:05:12,110
meeting.

349
01:05:12,160 --> 01:05:18,525
It's also very unlikely that you'll be blinded by Jesus and called to serve a particular

350
01:05:18,575 --> 01:05:24,939
people while out taking a walk.

351
01:05:24,989 --> 01:05:31,353
So how do we know?

352
01:05:31,403 --> 01:05:37,767
How do we know which ministry God is calling you to?

353
01:05:37,817 --> 01:05:44,182
How do we know if God is calling you to cross-cultural missions?

354
01:05:44,232 --> 01:05:50,596
Here's where I really want to take the mystery out of what it means to be called.

355
01:05:50,646 --> 01:05:57,010
And btw, this applies to any calling to any ministry, not just on missions, but yes,

356
01:05:57,060 --> 01:06:03,424
definitely for missions too.

357
01:06:03,474 --> 01:06:09,839
You discover the ministry God is calling you to in 3 phases: Learn, Discern, and Confirm.

358
01:06:09,889 --> 01:06:16,253
Learn: (Exploration) Posture of a student (for the youth here - this is important for

359
01:06:16,303 --> 01:06:22,667
you, but it's also a good reminder for the adults here): I'm here to explore.

360
01:06:22,717 --> 01:06:29,081
To discover.

361
01:06:29,131 --> 01:06:35,496
To Open yourself up to possibilities and make yourself available.

362
01:06:35,546 --> 01:06:41,910
A Willing heart to be used by God.

363
01:06:41,960 --> 01:06:48,324
A teachable heart.

364
01:06:48,374 --> 01:06:54,738
Much like the posture of Paul and Barnabas.

365
01:06:54,788 --> 01:07:01,153
I want to learn what God is doing in the World.

366
01:07:01,203 --> 01:07:07,567
See what He is already doing in different missions field.

367
01:07:07,617 --> 01:07:13,981
Find out what opportunities there are.

368
01:07:14,031 --> 01:07:20,395
Remember - God already has a plan - He's already working - through people, through

369
01:07:20,445 --> 01:07:26,810
organizations, through other churches.

370
01:07:26,860 --> 01:07:33,224
His plan is already enfolding.

371
01:07:33,274 --> 01:07:39,638
You're exploring how you can be part of God's plan.

372
01:07:39,688 --> 01:07:46,052
There are many ways to learn.

373
01:07:46,102 --> 01:07:52,467
Perspectives Class - how many have taken this?

374
01:07:52,517 --> 01:07:58,881
Esther and Pat and others organized this at our church last year.

375
01:07:58,931 --> 01:08:05,295
It's a great course.

376
01:08:05,345 --> 01:08:11,709
I would encourage you to take it the next time it's offered.

377
01:08:11,759 --> 01:08:18,124
Joshuaproject.net - a great website to learn about Go to missions conferences, Seattle

378
01:08:18,174 --> 01:08:24,538
has a yearly Missions Fest (see slide), For college students, check out Urbana, put on by

379
01:08:24,588 --> 01:08:30,952
InterVarsity - now every 3 years - so, if you're a junior or senior in High School - keep

380
01:08:31,002 --> 01:08:37,366
this in mind.

381
01:08:37,416 --> 01:08:43,781
It was an incredible experience when i was in college and still resonates with me even

382
01:08:43,831 --> 01:08:50,195
until today.

383
01:08:50,245 --> 01:08:56,609
Find out how God is already at work throughout the world and see if He may be calling you

384
01:08:56,659 --> 01:09:03,023
to join in what He is already doing.

385
01:09:03,073 --> 01:09:09,438
In the Learning phase, it's all about discovery.

386
01:09:09,488 --> 01:09:15,852
Then comes the next phase: Discern: - Holy Spirit, Prayer and Wise Counsel of others.

387
01:09:15,902 --> 01:09:22,266
Here's where you're figuring out what God is calling you to do.

388
01:09:22,316 --> 01:09:28,681
Passion - do I have a passion for this.

389
01:09:28,731 --> 01:09:35,095
God will rarely make you do something you hate.

390
01:09:35,145 --> 01:09:41,509
Gifting - Do I have the ability, the skills, the aptitude to do this?

391
01:09:41,559 --> 01:09:47,923
Ask yourself, does this ministry fit the way God made me?

392
01:09:47,973 --> 01:09:54,338
Opportunity - Is God presenting an opportunity for me to go?

393
01:09:54,388 --> 01:10:00,752
We see many examples in the Bible where sometimes God's call is just someone asking them

394
01:10:00,802 --> 01:10:07,166
to go.

395
01:10:07,216 --> 01:10:13,580
Barnabas went to Tarsus to find Paul to help in Antioch.

396
01:10:13,630 --> 01:10:19,995
In Paul's 2nd missionary journey in Acts 15, Paul chose Silas to go with him.

397
01:10:20,045 --> 01:10:26,409
Barnabas chose Mark to go another way.

398
01:10:26,459 --> 01:10:32,823
In Acts 16, Paul was in Lystra.

399
01:10:32,873 --> 01:10:39,237
He heard that Timothy had a good reputation so Paul asked Timothy to join him.

400
01:10:39,287 --> 01:10:45,652
For both Silas and Timothy, Paul's invitation was enough for them to go.

401
01:10:45,702 --> 01:10:52,066
Instead of waiting for some miraculous sign, look for opportunities.

402
01:10:52,116 --> 01:10:58,480
Pray - here's a dangerous thing you could do.

403
01:10:58,530 --> 01:11:04,894
You could ask God to show you opportunities to serve Him.

404
01:11:04,944 --> 01:11:11,309
You could ask God to open doors for you to go.

405
01:11:11,359 --> 01:11:17,723
Do Pray that God would open your eyes and open your heart to His missionary work.

406
01:11:17,773 --> 01:11:24,137
Holy Spirit - ask the Holy Spirit to guide you and lead you in Missions.

407
01:11:24,187 --> 01:11:30,551
Ask the Holy Spirit to reveal to you how you can fulfill the Great Commission.

408
01:11:30,601 --> 01:11:36,966
The Holy Spirit leads in a multitude of ways - from circumstances, opening and closing

409
01:11:37,016 --> 01:11:43,380
doors, speaking and convicting you in Scripture, to speaking directly to your soul in a

410
01:11:43,430 --> 01:11:49,794
way that only He can, including visions and miracles.

411
01:11:49,844 --> 01:11:56,208
Wise Counsel of others.

412
01:11:56,258 --> 01:12:02,623
One way the Holy Spirit can speak to you is through the wise counsel of others.

413
01:12:02,673 --> 01:12:09,037
Many times, I have asked mature brothers and sisters in Christ what they thought about my

414
01:12:09,087 --> 01:12:15,451
next steps.

415
01:12:15,501 --> 01:12:21,865
If I should step into a particular ministry.

416
01:12:21,915 --> 01:12:28,280
If I have the right skills and gifting for that.

417
01:12:28,330 --> 01:12:34,694
Confirm: For any ministry - try it out.

418
01:12:34,744 --> 01:12:41,108
Sometimes we just need to go and do.

419
01:12:41,158 --> 01:12:47,522
Whether that is serving in the church, serving in a particular ministry, or missions.

420
01:12:47,572 --> 01:12:53,937
And for missions, short term missions, mid term missions, is a great opportunity to

421
01:12:53,987 --> 01:13:00,351
explore if God is calling you to do missions work In doing the work, is the Holy Spirit

422
01:13:00,401 --> 01:13:06,765
confirming your choice?

423
01:13:06,815 --> 01:13:13,179
Are others affirming your calling and recognizing your role?

424
01:13:13,229 --> 01:13:19,594
Recently Steve Moy was just ordained.

425
01:13:19,644 --> 01:13:26,008
As he shared last week, it was a long journey that got him there.

426
01:13:26,058 --> 01:13:32,422
As part of his ordination, a council of Elders and Pastors met to confirm his calling as

427
01:13:32,472 --> 01:13:38,836
a Pastor.

428
01:13:38,886 --> 01:13:45,251
But here's the interesting thing about it.

429
01:13:45,301 --> 01:13:51,665
It's not like he wasn't already doing the work.

430
01:13:51,715 --> 01:13:58,079
He was!

431
01:13:58,129 --> 01:14:04,493
He was already doing the work of a pastor, a shepherd, an overseer.

432
01:14:04,543 --> 01:14:10,908
Part of his ordination is just a confirmation that he is called to serve as a pastor.

433
01:14:10,958 --> 01:14:17,322
You don't need to be ordained to do the work God is calling you to do.

434
01:14:17,372 --> 01:14:23,736
Try doing the ministry that you think God is leading you to do.

435
01:14:23,786 --> 01:14:30,150
See if that lines up with your gifting and if you have an aptitude for it.

436
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:36,565
See if you really have a passion for it.

437
01:14:36,615 --> 01:14:42,979
See if others recognize and affirm your calling to it.

438
01:14:43,029 --> 01:14:49,393
See if the Holy Spirit, in all the ways that He works, confirms your ministry.

439
01:14:49,443 --> 01:14:55,807
Let me conclude with this.

440
01:14:55,857 --> 01:15:02,222
Rick Warren again said - "A great commitment to the Great Commandment and the Great

441
01:15:02,272 --> 01:15:08,636
Commission will make you a great Christian." The Great Commandment - Love God with all

442
01:15:08,686 --> 01:15:15,050
your heart, soul, and mind, (and love others).

443
01:15:15,100 --> 01:15:21,464
The Great Commission - Go and make disciple of all nations - A commitment to both, will

444
01:15:21,514 --> 01:15:27,879
make you a great Christian.

445
01:15:27,929 --> 01:15:34,293
We are all called to fulfill the Great Commission.

446
01:15:34,343 --> 01:15:40,707
We need to discover how God will use us, our God given gifts, our resources, and our

447
01:15:40,757 --> 01:15:47,121
ability to share the Good News of Jesus around us and beyond us.

448
01:15:47,171 --> 01:15:53,536
Is God calling you to send?

449
01:15:53,586 --> 01:15:59,950
Is God calling you to go?
